article.description:
Jason Holsinger scored 18 points,
including four vital free throws in the last 11 seconds, as
Evansville fended off the Purdue Boilermakers for a 75-69 win
Saturday night.
article.headline: Holsinger, Gomez lead Evansville past Purdue
article.linkText: Holsinger, Gomez lead Evansville past Purdue
article.story: EVANSVILLE, Ind. (AP) -- Jason Holsinger scored 18 points, including four vital free throws in the last 11 seconds, as Evansville fended off the Purdue Boilermakers for a 75-69 win Saturday night. Victor Gomez had 12 points and four rebounds for the Purple Aces (2-2). Chris Lutz led Purdue with 14, followed by Matt Kiefer and Nate Minnoy with 12 each. The Purple Aces, who had a 27-21 margin at the break, led by as many as 12 in the second half before Purdue (2-3) rallied in the final five minutes. The Boilermakers shot just 7-of-20 (35 percent) in the first half but were 17-of-32 (53.1 percent) after the break. Lutz hit a 3-pointer with 4:26 left to trim the gap to two at 60-58, then Minnoy hit a jumper less than two minutes later to draw within one. Purdue stayed close and got to within two again with 54 seconds left on a Minnoy free throw. The Aces stretched their lead to six again, mostly on free throws, before Minnoy hit a layup to make it 71-69 with 16 seconds left. Purdue's Chris Hartley then fouled Holsinger twice, setting up the game-clinching free throws.
